Note: In the initial handling for 'C' case, we added n += 2 for "CIA" and n++ for "SCH" and "CH". Also added n++ for "PH" in 'P', and for 'S' case, separated SH and SIO/SIA with appropriate increments. For 'T', added n++ for "TH" and n += 2 for "TIA"/"TIO".

Also, we need to be careful with the 'C' case for "CI", "CE", "CY": they output 'S' and break, but they do not skip the vowel because the vowel is still part of the word and will be processed later? Actually, in standard Metaphone, "CI", "CE", "CY" produce 'S' for the C, and then the vowel is processed normally later. So no skip needed.

